You're running a version compiled with `go version => 1.2.1`. We support from go 1.3 and upward. Go 1.2 has indeed this issue.

You can uninstall the version from the repositories and install binaries with this:

```
sudo apt-get remove golang
[[ `uname -m` = "x86_64" ]] && GOARCH="amd64" || GOARCH="386"
wget https://storage.googleapis.com/golang/go1.4.2.linux-$GOARCH.tar.gz
sudo tar -C /usr/local -xzf go*.tar.gz
echo 'export GOPATH=$HOME/go' >> ~/.bashrc
echo 'export PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/go/bin:$GOPATH/bin' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc && go version
```

golang 1.4.2 is available in the ethereum ppa

```
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:ethereum/ethereum
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install golang
```
